Overview
This project is a basic car game built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Players control a car to avoid obstacles and score points. The car moves left and right to dodge incoming obstacles.
Features
A car that can be controlled by the player to move left and right.
Randomly generated obstacles that the player needs to avoid.
A scoring system to keep track of the player.
Game over screen and the option to restart the game.
Prerequisites
A code editor (e.g., Visual Studio Code).
A modern web browser (e.g., Chrome, Firefox).
Basic understanding of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
Getting Started
Clone or download this repository to our local machine.
Open the project folder our code edit
or .
Structure
index.html: The main HTML file that displays the game.
style.css: The CSS file  styling the game.
script.js: The JavaScript file  game logic.
Instructions
Open index.htmlin your web browser to play the game.
Use the left and right arrow keys to control the car.
Dodge the obstacles to score points.
When the game is over, we can restart by refreshing the page
Customization
we can customize the game by modifying the HTML, CSS, and JavaScript code. Here are some ideas for customization:

Change the car image and obstacles appearance.
Adjust the game difficulty by altering the speed and frequency of obstacles.
Add sound effects or background music.
Implement a high score system.
